$interpreted: Qilin Guard: So... you really saw her? Out on Hot Spring Street?
Baa Baa: You mean that girl everyone calls "Bluebird"? Course I've seen her!
Qilin Guard: Then could you introduce m— I mean, introduce my friend?
Baa Baa: Yeah, no worries, mate.
Qilin Guard: Wow, thank you so much! I can't wa— I mean, my friend can't wait...
Qilin Guard: Anyway, I'll keep my eyes and ears open for you. You should get back to the house. You don't want to get caught coming and going like this.
Baa Baa: Alright. Thanks for the help~
Tindoiimu: They...
Baa Baa: Don't worry~ One of the guards let me know, your friends both got away safely.
Baa Baa: And all those old guys from the Alliance are not happy about it.
Tindoiimu: Oh, that's great news!
Tindoiimu: Thank you, Baa Baa. I'm stuck in here and... without you, I'd be completely helpless.
Tindoiimu: I'm so sorry to get you involved, to get you trapped here with me...
Baa Baa: Eh, it's nothing. Being a merchant always has risks.
Baa Baa: And anyway, you gave me this.
Baa Baa: If there's ever money to be made, you know who to call.
Tindoiimu: You're so optimistic... it's impressive.
Baa Baa: Helps to be in this line of business, you know.
Baa Baa: I feel like... if you're sad, then go outside, breathe in the air, run around a bit... things will be alright.
Tindoiimu: When I would throw tantrums as a kid, my nanny would bring me out to the fields to play.
Tindoiimu: She was so great back then...
Tindoiimu: Really amazing.
Tindoiimu: Now I don't even know where she is...
Baa Baa: When you say nanny, do you mean that lady they mentioned before? Ji...Jiya something?
Tindoiimu: You mean Jiyanama!?
Baa Baa: That's the one!
Tindoiimu: Did they say where she was!?
Baa Baa: Ah, well... they... they said they were bringing her to Moya... to be executed...
Tindoiimu: ...Jiyanama... How could they...
Qilin Guard: Baa Baa!
Qilin Guard: Your papers checked out. Guess you really are just a merchant. You're free to go.
Baa Baa: Really!? Thank you!
Qilin Guard: And about everything you've seen here... Maybe just keep it to yourself, okay?
Baa Baa: No worries, cuz. I'll keep quiet.
Qilin Guard: Hmph, a demihuman merchant. Yeah, I'm sure you will keep quiet. Alright, get your stuff and go.
Tindoiimu: Baa Baa, you forgot this.
Baa Baa: ...What's this?
Tindoiimu: Isn't this that precious bracelet you were given by that princess? The one that's worth a lot of money?
Tindoiimu: If you forgot it, I wouldn't have any way of getting it back to you.
Tindoiimu: Remember, you said to call you if there's money to be made, right?
Baa Baa: Oh yeah! I just... took it out to show you! I almost forgot...! Thank you so much...
Qilin Guard: Hey, enough with the goodbyes! Go means go!
Baa Baa: Coming~
Qilin Guard: What's this?
Baa Baa: It's a little thank you for all your help. Some tea—silver pine.
Qilin Guard: Silver pine!? This is... thousands of Curren for a tael! Only mythics can afford this!
Baa Baa: Well, it's a gift, so just take it. I hope we can do business again in the future.
Qilin Guard: ...Thanks. Now let's get going.
Qilin Guard: I've heard silver pine tea can make you live longer. Commoners like us, we can't normally get our hands on stuff like this.
Qilin Guard: I've got to call over all the guys to have a cup!
Qilin Guard: Hmm... weird... why do I feel sleepy? Do you guys... also...
Qilin Guard: ...feel... slee.......
Tindoiimu: (They're snoring. I guess that's my cue...)
Qilin Guard: You guys drank all the tea without me!?
Qilin Guard: And then have the gall to take a NAP? Wake yourselves up right now!
Qilin Guard: Who's there!?
Baa Baa: Over here~ I've been waiting!
Tindoiimu: You understood!

Baa Baa: Hehe~ I took your payment, didn't I? Job's a job~ 
Lucky I had that tea, huh?
Tindoiimu: It worked like a charm, whatever it was.
Baa Baa: It actually was silver pine. People just don't know that when you mix it with hot water, the fumes knock you right out.
Baa Baa: I had gotten it for a client... But your bracelet should be worth more, anyway. Guess it's a win-win.
Baa Baa: Well, now that you're out, what's the plan?
Tindoiimu: ......
Baa Baa: Princess?
Tindoiimu: ...I have another job for you, if you're up to it...
Baa Baa: You want me to escort you back to the Insect Tribe?
Baa Baa: Or... you don't mean...!?
Tindoiimu: —I do... I want to go to Moya.
